-- To use the commands type the commands in chat with the prefix "+" with the command name like +speed, +snap etc
local players = game:GetService("Players")
local ReplicatedStorage = game:GetService("ReplicatedStorage")
local Admins = require(script.Parent.Admins)
local launchEvent = ReplicatedStorage:WaitForChild("launch")
local flingEvent = ReplicatedStorage:WaitForChild("fling")

-- Function to get target people so my life is easier
local function findTargets(sender, targetArg)
	targetArg = targetArg or "me"
	if targetArg == "me" then -- Returns the sender
		return {sender}
	elseif targetArg == "all" then -- Returns everyone
		return players:GetPlayers()
	elseif targetArg == "others" then -- Returns everyone except the sender
		local others = {}
		for _, plr in pairs(players:GetPlayers()) do
			if plr ~= sender then table.insert(others, plr) end
		end
		return others
	else -- If a player is specified return that player 
		local plr = players:FindFirstChild(targetArg)
		return plr and {plr} or {}
	end
end

-- Function to get all players
local function getAllPlayers()
	
	local characters = {} -- Array to store all characters
	
	for _, obj in pairs(game.Workspace:GetChildren()) do
		-- Checks if it is a model and a player
		if obj:IsA("Model") and obj:FindFirstChild("Humanoid") and game.Players:GetPlayerFromCharacter(obj) then
			table.insert(characters, obj)
		end
	end
	return characters 
end

local function distanceCheck(player: Player, distance: number) -- Function to check for the distance of every player
	local char = player.Character
	if not char then warn("Character not found for " .. player.Name) return end

	local hrp = char:FindFirstChild("HumanoidRootPart")
	if not hrp then warn("HumanoidRootPart not found for " .. player.Name ) return end

	local targets = {} -- Store all targets

	for _, character in pairs(workspace:GetChildren()) do
		if not character:IsA("Model") or character == char then continue end

		local hm, h = character:FindFirstChild("Humanoid"), character:FindFirstChild("HumanoidRootPart") -- Checks if the target has a humanoid and a hrp for error handling
		if not hm or not h then continue end

		if (hrp.Position - h.Position).Magnitude <= distance then -- Checks the distance before inserting them
			table.insert(targets, character)
		end
	end
	return targets -- Returns the targets
end

-- Function to get half of the players
local function getHalfOfPlayers(sender: Player, exclude: boolean)
	local characters = getAllPlayers()
	local chalf = {}

	local half = math.floor(#characters / 2) -- Gets half of the count of player stored in characters
	local i = 1

	while #chalf < half and i <= #characters do 
		if exclude and characters[i] == sender.Character then -- Skip if the sender if excluded == true
			i += 1
		else
			table.insert(chalf, characters[i])
			i += 1
		end
		task.wait()  
	end

	return chalf
end

-- To check if the player is allowed to use the rank cmd
local function Rank(player, requirement)
	if not Admins[player.Name] then return false end
	
	local rank = Admins[player.Name] or 0
	return rank >= requirement
end


local function apply(sender: Player, targetArg: SharedTable, callback)
	for _, plr in pairs(findTargets(sender, targetArg)) do -- Gets the targets first then returns the character or plr on the callback
		if plr.Character then
			callback(plr.Character, plr)
		end
	end
end

-- Sets walkspeed of the player
local function speed(char: Model, speed: number)
	local hum = char:FindFirstChild("Humanoid")
	if hum then 
		hum.WalkSpeed = speed 
	end
end

-- Kills the player
local function kill(char: Model)
	local hum = char:FindFirstChild("Humanoid")
	if hum then hum.Health = 0 end
end

-- Function for snap
local function snap(sender: Player)
	local chalf = getHalfOfPlayers(sender, true)
	for _, char in pairs(chalf) do
		local plr = game.Players:GetPlayerFromCharacter(char)
		plr:Kick("You got snapped out of existance") -- Kicks the player when affected
	end
end

--Toggles if the player can collide with other parts
local function noclip(char: Model, state: boolean)
	for _, part in ipairs(char:GetDescendants()) do
		if part:IsA("BasePart") then
			part.CanCollide = state
		end
	end
end

--Brings the targets to the sender
local function bring(sender: Player, targetChar: Model) -- 50
	local root = targetChar:FindFirstChild("HumanoidRootPart")
	local sRoot = sender.Character and sender.Character:FindFirstChild("HumanoidRootPart")
	if root and sRoot then
		root.CFrame = sRoot.CFrame
	end
end

-- Launches the player upwards
local function launch(char, player)
	if player then
		launchEvent:FireClient(player, player) -- It fires on the client because AssemblyLinearvelocity doesnt work on server
	else
		warn("Player is gone error") 
	end
end 

local angle = 0
local radius = 10
local orbitSpeed = 1
local Orbiting = {} -- Store all the players orbiting 

local function orbit(orbiter: Player, center: Model, state: Boolean)
	local orbiterChar = orbiter.Character
	local ohrp = orbiterChar:FindFirstChild("HumanoidRootPart")
	if not ohrp then warn("HumanoidRootPart not found for " .. orbiter.Name) return end
	
	local centerHrp = center:FindFirstChild("HumanoidRootPart")
	if not centerHrp then warn("HumanoidRootPart not found for " .. center.Name) return end
	Orbiting[orbiter.Name] = state
	if Orbiting[orbiter.Name] then
		game["Run Service"].Heartbeat:Connect(function()
			if not Orbiting[orbiter.Name] then return end

			angle += orbitSpeed --Increase the angle
			-- Calculate Z and X offset from the center
			local Xoffset = math.cos(angle) * radius
			local Zoffset = math.sin(angle) * radius
			
			local pos = centerHrp.Position + Vector3.new(Xoffset, 0, Zoffset)
			-- Move the orbiter to this position
			ohrp.CFrame = CFrame.lookAt(pos, centerHrp.Position)
		end)
	end
end

-- Adds, removes, or sets the player's money to the given amount
local function money(player: Player, amount: number, operation: string)
	local lFolder = player:FindFirstChild("leaderstats")
	if not lFolder or not lFolder:FindFirstChild("Money") then return end

	local m = lFolder.Money
	if operation == "add" then
		m.Value += amount
	elseif operation == "remove" then
		m.Value -= amount
	else
		m.Value = amount
	end
end

-- Dictionary containg all commands
local commands = {
	
	-- Launch people to the air with a velocity of 5000
	launch = {
		run = function(sender, args)
			local target = args[2]
			apply(sender, target, function(char, plr)
				launch(char, plr)
			end)
		end,
		rank = Admins.VIP
	},
	
	-- Joke command where if people are 20 studs close to the sender they get slower
	youretooslow = {
		run = function(sender: Player)
			local victims = distanceCheck(sender, 25)
			if not victims then warn("No victims found") return end
			
			for _, victim in ipairs(victims) do
				speed(victim, 0)
			end
		end,
		
		rank = Admins.VIP 
	},
	-- Flings a player
	fling = {
		run = function(sender, args)
			
			local target, velocity = args[2], args[3] or 500
			apply(sender, target, function(char, plr)
				flingEvent:FireClient(plr, plr, velocity)
			end)
		end,
		rank = Admins.VIP
	},
	-- Makes a player orbits someone
	orbit = {
		run = function(sender, args)
			local target = args[2]
			
			apply(sender, target, function(char, plr)
				orbit(sender, char, true)
			end)
		end,
		rank = Admins.VIP
	},
	-- Unorbits a player
	unorbit = {
		run = function(sender, args)
			local target = args[2]
			apply(sender, target, function(char, plr)
				orbit(sender, char, false)
			end)
		end,
		rank = Admins.VIP
	},
	-- People can rank people below them
	rank = {
		run = function(sender, args)
			local target, rank = args[2], args[3] 
			
			if not Admins[rank] then return end
			
			if Rank(sender, Admins[rank]) then
				apply(sender, target, function(char, plr)
					if plr.Name == sender.Name then
						warn(plr.Name .. " tried to rank himself")
						return 
					end 
					
					if Admins[plr.Name] and Admins[sender.Name] and Admins[plr.Name] >= Admins[sender.Name] then
						warn(sender.Name .. " tried to rank someone who ranks higher than him")
						return
					end
					
					print(plr.Name .. tostring(sender))
					Admins.setRank(plr, rank)
				end)
			end
		end
	},
	-- Command to wipe out half of the players in the game
	snap = {
		run = function(sender)
			snap(sender)
		end,
		rank = Admins.Mod
	},
	
	-- Sets the speed of the player
	speed = {
		run = function(sender, args)
			local target, value = args[2], tonumber(args[3])
			if not value then return end
			apply(sender, target, function(char)
				speed(char, value)
			end)
		end,
		rank = Admins.Mod
	},
	
	-- Kills the player
	kill = {
		run = function(sender, args)
			local target = args[2]
			apply(sender, target, kill)
		end,
		rank = Admins.Mod
	},
	
	-- Toggles the player collision to false
	noclip = {
		run = function(sender, args)
			local target = args[2]
			apply(sender, target, function(char)
				noclip(char, false)
			end)
		end,
		rank = Admins.Mod
	},
	
	-- Toggles the player collision to true
	clip = {
		run = function(sender, args)
			local target = args[2]
			apply(sender, target, function(char)
				noclip(char, true)
			end)
		end,
		rank = Admins.Mod
	},
	
	-- Brings the targets to the player
	bring = {
		run = function(sender, args)
			local target = args[2]
			apply(sender, target, function(char)
				bring(sender, char)
			end)
		end,
		rank = Admins.Mod
	},
	
	kick = {
		run = function(sender, args)
			local target, reason = args[2], args[3]
			apply(sender, target, function(char, plr)
				reason = reason or "No reason specified"
				plr:Kick("You have been kicked by an administrator Reason: " .. reason)
			end)
		end,
		rank = Admins.Mod
	},
	
	-- Gives money
	givemoney = {
		run = function(sender, args)
			local target, value = args[2], tonumber(args[3])
			if not value then return end
			apply(sender, target, function(char, plr)
				money(plr, value, "add")
			end)
		end,
		rank = Admins.Admin
	},
	
	-- Removes money
	removemoney = {
		run = function(sender, args)
			local target, value = args[2], tonumber(args[3])
			if not value then return end
			apply(sender, target, function(char, plr)
				money(plr, value, "remove")
			end)
		end,
		rank = Admins.Admin
	},
	
	-- Sets money
	setmoney = {
		run = function(sender, args)
			local target, value = args[2], tonumber(args[3])
			if not value then return end
			apply(sender, target, function(char, plr)
				money(plr, value)
			end)
		end,
		rank = Admins.Admin
	}
}

return commands
